President Donald Trump has proclaimed May 21-27, 2017, as National Safe Boating Week in the United States. The proclamation emphasizes the importance of boating safety and encourages Americans to learn about safe boating practices. The U.S. Coast Guard and its partners are promoting basic safety procedures, such as wearing life jackets, carrying emergency equipment, attending boating courses, and staying sober while navigating. The proclamation also recognizes that human error is a leading cause of boating accidents and highlights the potential life-saving benefits of wearing life jackets. The President calls on all Americans who participate in boating activities to observe this occasion and learn more about safe boating practices.